 Jewish literature make Homeless Tongues a timely and unusual intervention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aHebrew poetry, ModernxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aHebrew poetry, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish poetryxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aJewish poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLadino poetryxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aLadino poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMultilingualism and literature. 0aSephardic authorsxLanguage. 4aDiaspora. 4aJuan Gelman. 4aLadino. 4aMargalit Matitiahu. 4aSadia Lévy. 4aSephardic. 4aintertext. 4aminor literatures. 4apoetry. 4atransnational. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804797498zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804797498423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804797498.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles